# sent_id = 65
# text = The Presidency therefore proposes in a spirit of compromise to include services using E2EE in the scope of standard detection orders issued to high-risk services, under the condition that a detection order should not create any obligation that would require a provider to create access to end-to-end-encrypted data and that the technologies used for detection are vetted with regard to their effectiveness, their impact on fundamental rights and risks to cyber security.
